    {
      "id": "Dd4OT_TafgbDn_wq6kLsU",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 63.651533067163655,
      "y": 754.1692223036649,
      "width": 540,
      "height": 380,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": "jnbUQWgj3Dhjrky5bH0ug",
      "index": "a9V",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1295897247,
      "version": 3289,
      "versionNonce": 2097449441,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774426517359,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The data reveals a dynamic pattern in Monthly Recurring Revenue\n(MRR) over the observed period. In the most recent month,\nFebruary 2026, MRR fluctuated significantly, starting at\n**$13,160** on February 1 and peaking at **$84,357** on February\n4. This peak was followed by a sharp decline to **$21,336** on\nFebruary 6, illustrating volatility. The month ended with MRR at\n**$51,238** on February 16, showing a recovery from mid-month\nlows.\n\nComparing year-over-year data, February 2025 also exhibited\nfluctuations, with MRR ranging from **$9,824** to **$72,078**.\nNotably, February 2026's peak was higher than any day in February\n2025, indicating potential growth in revenue capacity.\n\nThroughout the data, there are frequent spikes and drops,\nsuggesting that MRR is subject to significant variability, possibly\ndue to seasonal factors or business cycles. The data highlights the\nimportance of monitoring these fluctuations to understand\nunderlying business dynamics and potential growth opportunities.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The data reveals a dynamic pattern in Monthly Recurring Revenue (MRR) over the observed period. In the most recent month, February 2026, MRR fluctuated significantly, starting at **$13,160** on February 1 and peaking at **$84,357** on February 4. This peak was followed by a sharp decline to **$21,336** on February 6, illustrating volatility. The month ended with MRR at **$51,238** on February 16, showing a recovery from mid-month lows.\n\nComparing year-over-year data, February 2025 also exhibited fluctuations, with MRR ranging from **$9,824** to **$72,078**. Notably, February 2026's peak was higher than any day in February 2025, indicating potential growth in revenue capacity.\n\nThroughout the data, there are frequent spikes and drops, suggesting that MRR is subject to significant variability, possibly due to seasonal factors or business cycles. The data highlights the importance of monitoring these fluctuations to understand underlying business dynamics and potential growth opportunities.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
